    <chapter>
      <heading>
        Software documentation for the TTIOSpectrumIndex class
      </heading>
      <class name="TTIOSpectrumIndex" super="NSObject">
        <declared>TTIOSpectrumIndex.h</declared>
        <desc>
          Per-spectrum offsets, lengths, and queryable
          scan metadata for one TTIOAcquisitionRun. Kept as
          parallel C arrays inside NSData buffers for compact
          storage and fast iteration. Persisted as five
          parallel 1-D HDF5 datasets under the run's
          `spectrum_index/` sub-group plus a sixth
          one for precursor charge. Range queries (RT, ms_level,
          polarity) operate on the in-memory arrays and do
          not touch the signal channels — this is the
          "compressed-domain query" property of the
          MPEG-G access-unit model. API status: Stable.
          Cross-language equivalents: Python:
          ttio.acquisition_run.SpectrumIndex
          Java: global.thalion.ttio.SpectrumIndex
        </desc>
        <method type="instancetype" factory="yes">
          <sel>readFromGroup:</sel>
          <arg type="TTIOHDF5Group*">parent</arg>
          <sel>error:</sel>
          <arg type="NSError**">error</arg>
          <desc>
            <em>Description forthcoming.</em>
          </desc>
        </method>
        <method type="instancetype" factory="yes">
          <sel>readFromStorageGroup:</sel>
